<paragraph id="8BB6368C9259773BFF43FCA6FC94BFB3" blockId="9.[136,1452,158,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFF43FCA6FE2BBFDB" bold="true" box="[189,442,886,912]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFE44FCA6FD33BFDB" box="[442,674,886,912]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9259773BFE29FCA6FD33BFDB" box="[471,674,886,912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">Bertolonia bullata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
occur in severely fragmented areas on high elevation (
<quantity id="4CF19B699259773BFAEAFCA6FA31BFDA" box="[1300,1440,886,913]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" unit="m" value="750.0" valueMax="1000.0" valueMin="500.0">500–1000m</quantity>
). It has been collected within the “Reserva Particular do Patrimônio Natural Serra Bonita” and in the “Parque Nacional Serra das Lontras”. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9259773BFE92FC6BFDAABF9E" box="[364,571,955,981]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFE92FC6BFDAABF9E" box="[364,571,955,981]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Bertolonia bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an EOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B699259773BFD07FC6CFCF5BF93" box="[761,868,956,984]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9769999999999999" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" unit="km" value="1977.0">1,977 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B699259773BFBF5FC6CFBF2BF93" box="[1035,1123,956,984]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.78" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" unit="km" value="378.0">378 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Endangered” (EN), following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D9259773BFE11FC0EFD14BFB3" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[495,645,990,1016]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31365079259773BFF43FBD1FDDCB918" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB6368C9259773BFF43FBD1FDDCB918" blockId="9.[136,1452,158,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFF43FBD1FE98B850" bold="true" box="[189,265,1025,1051]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9259773BFED8FBD1FE65B850" box="[294,500,1025,1051]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFED8FBD1FE65B850" box="[294,500,1025,1051]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Bertolonia bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E9259773BFD67FBD1FD4CB850" box="[665,733,1025,1051]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation id="13322A099259773BFB99FBD1FB29B850" box="[1127,1208,1025,1051]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[341,1239,654,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-255@5.[340,1247,641,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A. Bertolonia alternifolia. B. Bertolonia angustipetala. C. Bertolonia bullata. D. Bertolonia carmoi. E. Bertolonia cuspidata. F. Bertolonia hirsutissima. G. Bertolonia igrapiuna. H. Bertolonia kollmannii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597686/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
), in humid and shady areas in the southeastern portion of the state. Collected with flowers in November and December, and fruits from August to April. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9259773BFEBDFB96FD81B82B" box="[323,528,1094,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFEBDFB96FD81B82B" box="[323,528,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Bertolonia bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the leaf blade with dark green, bullate adaxial surface, sparsely glandulose-punctate and glandulose-villose (trichomes 
<quantity id="4CF19B699259773BFCF9FBB9FC05B8C8" box="[775,916,1129,1156]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="1.5">1.5–3.5 mm</quantity>
long), and by the stem, abaxial leaf surface, hypanthium and sepals only glandulose-punctate. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9259773BFD43FB5BFC1DB8EE" box="[701,908,1163,1189]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFD43FB5BFC1DB8EE" box="[701,908,1163,1189]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Bertolonia bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9259773BFBDDFB5CFA3DB8EE" authority="Bacci &amp; Michelangeli" authorityName="Bacci &amp; Michelangeli" box="[1059,1452,1163,1190]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFBDDFB5CFB3BB8EE" box="[1059,1194,1164,1189]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">B. vitoriana</emphasis>
Bacci &amp; Michelangeli
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D9259773BFF53FB7EFE33B883" author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[173,418,1198,1225]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFF0CFB7FFEB3B883" box="[242,290,1198,1224]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">et al</emphasis>
. 2018: 788
</bibRefCitation>
). Both have the stem, abaxial leaf surface, hypanthium and sepals glandulose-punctate, petals with an apiculate apex, anthers with an introrse pore and the connective prolonged below the thecae. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9259773BFB21FB01FA3AB8A0" box="[1247,1451,1233,1259]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFB21FB01FA3AB8A0" box="[1247,1451,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Bertolonia bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9259773BFEEAFB24FE0BB946" box="[276,410,1268,1293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFEEAFB24FE0BB946" box="[276,410,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">B. vitoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the bullate leaf surface (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFD31FB24FD77B946" box="[719,742,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">vs</emphasis>
. flat in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9259773BFCC2FB24FC50B946" box="[828,961,1268,1293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFCC2FB24FC50B946" box="[828,961,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">B. vitoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and petioles and adaxial surface of the leaf blade glandulose-villose (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFE56FAC7FE2EB97B" box="[424,447,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">vs</emphasis>
. petioles and adaxial surface of the leaf blade only glandulose-punctate). For more details, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D9259773BFF4DFAE9FE2CB918" author="Baumgratz, J. F. A. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Jardim, A. B." box="[179,445,1337,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" pagination="273 - 279" refId="ref18825" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A., Amorim, A. M. &amp; Jardim, A. B. (2011) Two new species of Bertolonia (Melastomataceae) from the Brazilian Atlantic Forest. Kew Bulletin 66: 273 - 279. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 011 - 9281 - 0" type="journal article" year="2011">
Baumgratz 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9259773BFECBFAEAFEF7B918" box="[309,358,1337,1363]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">et al</emphasis>
. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation id="C68B03379259773BFE0DFAE9FDD6B918" box="[499,583,1337,1363]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
